page.title: 06 Ecology_Shore birds
page.content: The heron jabs fish with its sharp beak and takes them back to its young ,who are nesting in the tree_tops.The heron has long legs to enable it to stand in shallow water. The redshank has long red legs like its beak, and is black and grey with grey spots on its black back. The swans diet is much the same as the herons although the swan nests in tall reeds. The dipper is brown and black with a white breast. It catches its fish by suddenly dipping his head in the water. The sandpiper is grey_brown with a white breast.It flies low over the water with flickering wings. Other birds in this area are shearwater, goose ,oyster catcher, seagull, coot,moor hen,duck.
